{"word":"πανώλεθρος","slug":"πανώλεθρος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>πανώλεθρος</b></el> <el>(πᾰν-ώλεθρος, ον,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ὄλεθρος'><el>ὄλεθρος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>utterly ruined, utterly destroyed</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>; <el>πανωλέθρους ὀλέσθαι</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; <el>π. πίπτειν</el> <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>in moral sense, <i>utterly abandoned</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>perditissimus</el>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <i>all destructive, all-ruinous</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}